Aloe perryi

   [3039.jpg]
    Authority   Baker
      Family    Liliopsida:Liliidae:Asparagales:Asphodelaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3039

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is a succulent herbaceous plants, with, strong and
   fibrous roots and numerous, persistent, fleshy leaves, proceeding from
   the upper part of the root, narrow, tapering, thick and fleshy, usually
   beset at the edges with spiney teeth. USE: The leaves have medicinal
   properties. GROWING PERIOD: Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Socotrine aloe.
   FURTHER INF: Socotrine aloe is native of the Socatra Islands in the
   Indian Ocean.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   White F 1983 pp 115 255 [DRA, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DEP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 294 [USE]
   Duke J 1979 pp 97 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1982 pp 14

